review_blob: This is the Canadian version of their Budweiser brew. If anything, this has the bare minimum of any ingredient to make this brew good. When your touring canada, dont ask the locals whats the best canadian beer because this is what theyll tell you all while laughing behind your back!
Good brew. Great amount of bitterness for the hoppy flavor. A little pricey but when its on sale, its in my basket.
I only drink this brew in memory of my grandpa. He drank this stuff back in WWII and thats why I drink it. This beer sucks. Dont waste your money.

I love this brew. Not a HUGE fan of Samel Adams but this is a really good one. Its festive, has a great taste, and easy to drink. I like this brew at room temperature rather than cold but either way, you cant go wrong with this brew.
Out of all the malt liquors, Id say Michkeys is the best. Its nothing spectacular but gets the job done. Never been fond of the grenades but love the 40s. I feel like a real man with a 40 oz bottle.

This beer sucks. Nothing good about this other than its cheap and is fun to play Edward 40 Hands. The smell is horrible. The taste is horrible. (Especially in a 40 oz, the last swig to end it is always the hardest) When I was poor, this was my drink of choice but now I can affoard some better brews and its totally worth it than buying this trash.
This beer isnt THAT BAD... Its more of something cool to try but nothing spectacular. I dont even know if it has alcohol because I didnt feel a damn thing!
This beer is O.K..... Its nothing to brag about. For sure, your drinking quality but its not all THAT GREAT

The only thing good about this beer is the story behind the history of this beer. Its a cute story of Might Arrow who used to roam the brewery and blah blah blah but other than that, this brew is nothing to brag about.

Dont judge a book by its cover. The olive green and dookie brown lable detered me for the longest till I actually tried it and I was amazed. Its for sure one of my top IPAs that I enjoy drinking. This is not for the weak but for those of us who enjoy quality, you wont regret it.
I look forward to this brew every year. Its so flavorful and the color is so beautiful. Get it, you wont regret it.
By far, the best Samuel Adams you can get. It tastes so delish and really easy to drink. Id suggest not drinking this with a bowl of spaghetti but its sure is tempting.
Fuckin awesome beer. Goes down smooth and easy to drink. Great with meat but not with pasta.
Damn good Indian beer. It taste really good with some spicey ass food. I cant find it anywhere unless its at an Indian restaraunt.
If your a veteran, cheers to this brew. Its a little pricey but well worth it. I think its a true American beer.
This beer is a typical beer from Holland. It doesnt taste real spectacular. Use your money to buy a lottery ticket when you come across this beer.
Freakin awesome IPA. I wish I could freeze it on a lake and skate on it and then watch it melt in the spring time so we can drink it!
This beer is a lager but its just too stinky as are most lagers are. It has a great color but thats about it.
This beer will knock your socks off. Its so good. Really thick and bitter but has a great taste. For beer lovers, I think youll enjoy this one.
On St. Pattys day, instead of having a green Coors Light, drink a real mans drink. Murphys Irish stout. Itll make your empty stomach full.
On St. Pattys day, instead of getting one of those green Bud Light beers, have a Murphys Irish Red. Itll put hair on your chest.

This beer sucks. The orange is too overpowering for this brew. Its not anything to brag about. Its so overpowering with the orange flavor that Id rather have a real orange this this crap for beer. A waste of money and a waste of time. Take my word for it. DONT BUY IT...

surprised ratings seem so low for this...pours light amber with medium-sized white head..aroma of caramel malt and pine hops..flavor is heavy in pine and citrus, little malt, and a bitter, nutty finish...not bad and quite quaffable
SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS SUCKS!!!!
Best damn beer Trader Joes has to offer. It taste great, gets tow up from the flow up.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Its a cider but thats about all it is. I dont really understand ciders so dont take my word for it.
Great beer. Top Shelf status. The smell of the brew is so great. It has so many flavors I cant explain. Good stuff.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: This IPA is freakin awesome. Has a great taste with awesome flavor. Its just right when it comes to the hops.

I dont care what anyone says. Lone Star is the heart of Texas Pride. I live in California but was born and raised in Texas and this brew always makes me feel right at home. When your 15 beers down, the puzzles on the bottom of the bottle caps are hard as hell!
Boddingtons is a smooth beer. A really think head, light on the hops, taste really creamy and good. Youll enjoy.

If I remember correct, this is Pizza Orgasmicas only beer that is above 6% so a few pints of these, your going to get $&%@ed up! Overall, I think its a good brew. Hoppy, great head, color is awesome. You cant go wrong.

I wasnt too satisfied with this brew. Its not at all what you would expect. Not too much flavor. When I drank this, its more like your drinking JUST BEER and thats it. Pizza Orgasmica has better quality beers than this one.
I love the peach follow through with this beer. Its very light, you can almost chug it but why waste your money that way? Its totally awesome. Id recommend it.
Its not an exciting beer but its very smooth. Not too much head. Easy beer to drink. Very malty.
This beer taste great with some spicey ass Indian food. Its not too flavorful but it does the job.
This beer is nothing to brag about. Someone below said its not a skunky lager like most lagers are and its true. Id have this after running 6 miles to rehydrate.
Good beer but extremely malty. I would not recommend having an entire 6 pack like I did. It will give you one of the worst hang overs and give you the shits the next day.
Im not a big fan of this particular beer. Its just not in my taste buds. Its not too heavy. Has a dry flavor but doesnt really do it to me for the hops.
This is an O.K. IPA. Nothing exciting. Hoppy but thats about it. I will get it if there is nothing else there but not my first choice of brew.

Ill be honest. I didnt want to buy this beer because who wants a bottle with a bunch of grass around it but when I bought it, its actually a very good brew. Great for a hot day after actually cutting the grass. Its smooth, easy to drink, one of a kind.
This is a great brew. Hops are strong. Has a great taste. I think somewhat bitter but very smooth.
If your looking for a GREAT IPA, you wont find it here. Yes its Hoppy and has a great color but this brew is quite boring and nothing exciting.
I accidentally ordered this thinking it was the IPA but turned out to be the Cider. Not too bad. Im not a cider type and to me, all ciders taste the same so dont take my word for it.

Out of all the Shiners, I think this one is the worst. The taste sucks. I usually dont put lemons in my hefeweizens but I think I need an entire lemon just to give it some flavor. Litlle bit of advice, keep your money.
Damn good brew. The aroma is awesome, the taste is great, very hoppy, your definately drinking some quality when it comes to this.
crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap crap.

I had this beer when I was about 22 years old. Maybe I was too young to know to see what it was all about but all I remember was the alcohol burned down like I had a shot of vodka rather than a drink of beer. Got drunk after 2 cans. Good for a young buck that wants to get drunk fast.
I hate this beer. Its the budlight of beer from Holland. If this is the only thing in the store, then find a new store.

This is a very good stout. It has a smooth malty flavor. I think it taste great warm. Find it at Trader Joes.

Cheers!
I was expecting good things from Samuel Adams when it came to having an IPA. Its hoppy and has a good head but thats about it. Theres nothing exciting or memorable about this beer.
